  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0bca\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd  \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc0\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb2\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Passport office in Jaffna at own expense",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Investment Promotion Minister Dammika Perera said today (28) that the one-day passport issuance service would be launched in three more districts from next Monday (04) with his own funds to open a passport office branch in Jaffna.",
        "The one day service will be at the branch offices of the Department of Immigration and Emigration in Matara, Kandy and Vavuniya.",
        "As the Minister in charge of the Department, he stated that he intends to open five more branch offices in Sri Lanka and the President pointed out the need to open such offices.",
        "He said he would open his first passport office branch in Jaffna using his own funds as it would take six months or more to call for bids.",
        "The minister also said he was looking into accepting donations or using his own funds to open the remaining offices."
      ],
